MLA = [
    ensemble.AdaBoostClassifier(),
    ensemble.BaggingClassifier(),
    ensemble.GradientBoostingClassifier(),
    ensemble.RandomForestClassifier(),
    linear_model.LogisticRegressionCV(),
    neighbors.KNeighborsClassifier(),
    svm.SVC(probability=True),
    svm.LinearSVC(),   
    tree.DecisionTreeClassifier(),
    discriminant_analysis.LinearDiscriminantAnalysis(),
    discriminant_analysis.QuadraticDiscriminantAnalysis(),
    XGBClassifier()
    ]

cv_split = model_selection.ShuffleSplit(n_splits = 10, test_size = .3, train_size = .6, random_state = 0)
MLA_columns = ['MLA Name','MLA Train Accuracy Mean', 'MLA Test Accuracy Mean', 'MLA Test Accuracy 3*STD' ,'MLA Time']
MLA_compare = pd.DataFrame(columns = MLA_columns)


MLA_predict = y_train[y]


row_index = 1
for alg in MLA:

 
    MLA_name = alg.__class__.__name__
    MLA_compare.loc[row_index, 'MLA Name'] = MLA_name
    
   
    cv_results = model_selection.cross_validate(alg,x_train[x],  y_train[y], cv  = cv_split, return_train_score=True)

    MLA_compare.loc[row_index, 'MLA Time'] = cv_results['fit_time'].mean()
    MLA_compare.loc[row_index, 'MLA Train Accuracy Mean'] = cv_results['train_score'].mean()
    MLA_compare.loc[row_index, 'MLA Test Accuracy Mean'] = cv_results['test_score'].mean()   
    
    MLA_compare.loc[row_index, 'MLA Test Accuracy 3*STD'] = cv_results['test_score'].std()*3


    alg.fit(x_train[x],  y_train[y])
    MLA_predict[MLA_name] = alg.predict(x_train[x])
    
    row_index+=1


MLA_compare.sort_values(by = ['MLA Test Accuracy Mean'], ascending = False, inplace = True)
MLA_compare

MLA = [
    ensemble.AdaBoostClassifier(),
    ensemble.BaggingClassifier(),
    ensemble.GradientBoostingClassifier(),
    ensemble.RandomForestClassifier(),

    linear_model.LogisticRegressionCV(),
    
    neighbors.KNeighborsClassifier(),
    
    svm.SVC(probability=True),
    svm.LinearSVC(),
    
    tree.DecisionTreeClassifier(),
    
    discriminant_analysis.LinearDiscriminantAnalysis(),
    discriminant_analysis.QuadraticDiscriminantAnalysis(),

    XGBClassifier()
    ]

cv_split = model_selection.ShuffleSplit(n_splits = 10, test_size = .3, train_size = .6, random_state = 0 ) 

MLA_columns = ['MLA Name','MLA Train Accuracy Mean', 'MLA Test Accuracy Mean', 'MLA Test Accuracy 3*STD' ,'MLA Time']
MLA_compare = pd.DataFrame(columns = MLA_columns)

MLA_predict = y_train4[y]

row_index = 1
for alg in MLA:

    MLA_name = alg.__class__.__name__
    MLA_compare.loc[row_index, 'MLA Name'] = MLA_name
    
    cv_results = model_selection.cross_validate(alg,x_train4[x],  y_train4[y], cv  = cv_split, return_train_score=True)

    MLA_compare.loc[row_index, 'MLA Time'] = cv_results['fit_time'].mean()
    MLA_compare.loc[row_index, 'MLA Train Accuracy Mean'] = cv_results['train_score'].mean()
    MLA_compare.loc[row_index, 'MLA Test Accuracy Mean'] = cv_results['test_score'].mean()   
    MLA_compare.loc[row_index, 'MLA Test Accuracy 3*STD'] = cv_results['test_score'].std()*3
    

    alg.fit(x_train4[x],  y_train4[y])
    MLA_predict[MLA_name] = alg.predict(x_train4[x])
    
    row_index+=1

MLA_compare.sort_values(by = ['MLA Test Accuracy Mean'], ascending = False, inplace = True)

perf = ['above', 'average', 'below', 'excellent', 'poor']

for ind in range(len(confmatrices3)):
    df_cm = pd.DataFrame(confmatrices3[ind], index = [i for i in perf], columns = [i for i in perf])
    plt.figure(figsize = (10,7))
    ax = plt.axes()
